IsEmailBounced.title: Is Email Bounced

Jigsaw.title: Data.com Key
Jigsaw.description: References the company’s ID in Data.com. If an account has a value in this field, it means that the account was imported from Data.com. If the field value is null, the account wasn’t imported from Data.com. Maximum size is 20 characters. Available in API version 22.0 and later. Label is Data.com Key. Important The Jigsaw field is exposed in the API to support troubleshooting for import errors and reimporting of corrected data. Do not modify this value.

Pronouns.title: Pronouns
Pronouns.description: The contact’s personal pronouns, reflecting their gender identity. Others can use these pronouns to refer to the contact in the third person. The entry is selected from a picklist of available values, which the administrator sets. Maximum 40 characters.

GenderIdentity.title: Gender Identity
GenderIdentity.description: The contact’s internal experience of their gender, which may or may not correspond to their designated sex at birth.

table.name: Account
table.description: Represents an individual account, which is an organization or person involved with your business (such as customers, competitors, and partners).

Id.title: Account ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Name.title: Account Name
Name.description: Required. Label is Account Name. Name of the account. Maximum size is 255 characters. If the account has a record type of Person Account: This value is the concatenation of the FirstName, MiddleName, LastName, and Suffix of the associated person contact. You can't modify this value.

LastName.title: Last Name
LastName.description: Required. Label is Account Name. Name of the account. Maximum size is 255 characters. If the account has a record type of Person Account: This value is the concatenation of the FirstName, MiddleName, LastName, and Suffix of the associated person contact. You can't modify this value.

FirstName.title: First Name
FirstName.description: Required. Label is Account Name. Name of the account. Maximum size is 255 characters. If the account has a record type of Person Account: This value is the concatenation of the FirstName, MiddleName, LastName, and Suffix of the associated person contact. You can't modify this value.

Salutation.title: Salutation
Salutation.description: Required. Label is Account Name. Name of the account. Maximum size is 255 characters. If the account has a record type of Person Account: This value is the concatenation of the FirstName, MiddleName, LastName, and Suffix of the associated person contact. You can't modify this value.

Type.title: Account Type
Type.description: Type of account, for example, Customer, Competitor, or Partner.

Sic.description: Standard Industrial Classification code of the company’s main business categorization, for example, 57340 for Electronics. Maximum of 20 characters. This field is available on business accounts, not person accounts.

Ownership.title: Ownership
Ownership.description: Ownership type for the account, for example Private, Public, or Subsidiary.

TickerSymbol.title: Ticker Symbol
TickerSymbol.description: The stock market symbol for this account. Maximum of 20 characters. This field is available on business accounts, not person accounts.

Description.title: Account Description
Description.description: Text description of the account. Limited to 32,000 KB.

Rating.title: Account Rating
Rating.description: The account’s prospect rating, for example Hot, Warm, or Cold.

Site.title: Account Site
Site.description: Name of the account’s location, for example Headquarters or London. Label is Account Site. Maximum of 80 characters.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

LastActivityDate.title: Last Activity
LastActivityDate.description: Value is one of the following, whichever is the most recent: Due date of the most recent event logged against the record. Due date of the most recently closed task associated with the record.

IsPartner.title: Partner Account
IsPartner.description: Indicates whether the account has at least one contact enabled to use the org's partner portal (true) or not (false). This field is available if partner relationship management (partner portal) is enabled OR digital experiences is enabled and you have partner portal licenses.If you change this field's value from true to false, you can disable up to 15 partner portal users associated with the account and permanently delete all of the account's partner portal roles and groups. You can't restore deleted partner portal roles and groups. Disabling a partner portal user in the Salesforce user interface or the API doesn’t change this field's value from true to false. Even if this field's value is false, you can enable a contact on an account as a partner portal user via the API. Exclude this field when merging accounts. This field can be updated in API version 16.0 and later. Tip We recommend that you update up to 50 contacts simultaneously when changing the accounts on contacts enabled for an Experience Cloud site. We also recommend that you make this update after business hours.

IsCustomerPortal.title: Customer Portal Account
IsCustomerPortal.description: Indicates whether the account has at least one contact enabled to use the org's Experience Cloud site or Customer Portal (true) or not (false). This field is available if Customer Portal is enabled OR digital experiences is enabled.If your org is enabled to use Content Security Policy (CSP) features, then this field is visible on the Account object even if those features are later disabled. If you change this field's value from true to false, you can disable up to 100 Experience Cloud site or Customer Portal users associated with the account and permanently delete all of the account's site roles and groups. You can't restore deleted site roles and groups. Exclude this field when merging accounts. This field can be updated in API version 16.0 and later. Tip We recommend that you update up to 50 contacts simultaneously when changing the accounts on contacts enabled for an Experience Cloud site. We also recommend that you make this update after business hours.

IsPersonAccount.description: Read only. Label is Is Person Account. Indicates whether this account has a record type of Person Account (true) or not (false).

ChannelProgramName.title: Channel Program Name
ChannelProgramName.description: Read only. Name of the channel program the account has enrolled. If this account has enrolled more than one channel program, the oldest channel program name is displayed.

ChannelProgramLevelName.title: Channel Program Level Name
ChannelProgramLevelName.description: Read only. Name of the channel program level the account has enrolled. If this account has enrolled more than one channel program level, the oldest channel program name is displayed.

Id.title: Insurance Policy Coverage ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Name.title: Name
Name.description: An auto-generated number assigned to this record.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

CategoryCode.title: Category Code
CategoryCode.description: A carrier-specific code that identifies the coverage. For example, benefit, clause, or deductible.

LimitRange.title: Limit Range
LimitRange.description: The range of the coverage limit. For example, bodily injury coverage with limits as USD 100,000 per person and USD 300,000 per accident.

LimitAmount.title: Limit Amount
LimitAmount.description: The limit of the fixed coverage amount. For example, uninsured motorist coverage of USD 1000.

LimitDate.title: Limit Date
LimitDate.description: The date from which the coverage limit is in effect. For example, an annuity benefit is valid only after the insured is 60 years old.

LimitPercentage.title: Limit Percentage
LimitPercentage.description: The percentage of the actuals covered by this coverage.

PremiumAmount.title: Premium Amount
PremiumAmount.description: The premium paid by the customer for this coverage.

DeductibleAmount.title: Deductible Amount
DeductibleAmount.description: The deductible amount that the customer must pay.

Category.title: Category
Category.description: The category that the coverage belongs to. For example, benefit, clause, deductible, rider.

CategoryGroup.title: Category Group
CategoryGroup.description: The specific category group. For example, for a liability coverage record, benefit is the category and liability is the category group.

CategoryGroupType.title: Category Group Type
CategoryGroupType.description: The type of the category group.

Discount.title: Discount
Discount.description: The discount that was given on the coverage or the benefit.

BenefitPaymentFrequency.title: Benefit Payment Frequency
BenefitPaymentFrequency.description: The frequency of the payment if the benefit or coverage entails a recurring payout to the insured. For example, monthly, semi-monthly, quarterly, semi-annually, or annually.

EffectiveDate.title: Effective Date
EffectiveDate.description: The date from which the coverage is in effect.

ExpirationDate.title: Expiration Date
ExpirationDate.description: The date on which the coverage expires.

IncomeOptionType.title: Income Option Type
IncomeOptionType.description: The type of the income option given to the policy participant. For example, periodic payment is an income option type, and annuity is an income option.

DeathBenefitOptionType.title: Death Benefit Option Type
enum: Decreasing based on a commuted value
enumNames: Decreasing based on a commuted value
DeathBenefitOptionType.description: The method for the payment of death benefit.

SourceSystemIdentifier.title: Source System Identifier
SourceSystemIdentifier.description: The ID of this coverage record in the source system.

SourceSystem.title: Source System
SourceSystem.description: The name of the source system this record was obtained from.

StandardPremiumAmount.title: Standard Premium
StandardPremiumAmount.description: The expected premium for the policy over the policy period. This field is available from API version 51.0 and later.

StandardTaxAmount.title: Standard Tax
StandardTaxAmount.description: The expected tax on the policy over the policy period. This field is available from API version 51.0 and later.

StandardFeeAmount.title: Standard Fee
StandardFeeAmount.description: The expected fee for the policy over the policy period. This field is available from API version 51.0 and later.

TermFeeAmount.title: Term Fee
TermFeeAmount.description: The expected fee for the policy over the policy period, prorated based on the policy's effective dates. This field is available from API version 51.0 and later.

TermPremiumAmount.title: Term Premium
TermPremiumAmount.description: The expected premium for the policy over the policy period, prorated based on the policy's effective dates. This field is available from API version 51.0 and later.

TermTaxAmount.title: Term Tax
TermTaxAmount.description: The expected tax on the policy over the policy period, prorated based on the policy's effective dates. This field is available from API version 51.0 and later.

TotalStandardAmount.title: Total Standard Amount
TotalStandardAmount.description: The sum of the expected premium, fee, and tax for the policy over the policy period. This field is available from API version 51.0 and later.

CoverageCode.title: Coverage Code
CoverageCode.description: The unique code of the insurance policy coverage across all the policy versions.

schema.description: [Service Cloud] An Incident is any unplanned business interruption that has wide-sweeping impacts and requires an urgent fix. This object contains the details of the incident, documenting the history of the incident from registration to closure.

Id.title: Incident ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

Subject.description: A brief description of the incident.

Description.title: Description
Description.description: A description of the incident. This field can store up to 32 KB of data, but only the first 255 characters appear in reports.

DetectedDateTime.description: The date and time (in UTC) when the incident was first detected.

StartDateTime.title: Start Date Time
StartDateTime.description: The date and time (in UTC) when the incident began.

EndDateTime.title: End Date Time
EndDateTime.description: The date and time (in UTC) when the incident ended.

ResolutionDateTime.description: The date and time (in UTC) when the incident was resolved.

Status.title: Status
Status.description: Any custom or granular stages a customer may want to track.

Urgency.title: Urgency
Urgency.description: A measure of how long the resolution can be delayed until an incident, problem, or change has a significant business impact.

Priority.title: Priority
Priority.description: The impact and urgency of the incident.

ReportedMethod.title: Reported Method
ReportedMethod.description: Indicates how the incident was reported to customer service.

Type.title: Type
Type.description: The type of incident, for example, question or problem. Administrators set field values.

SubCategory.title: Sub Category
SubCategory.description: The type of incident. One level deeper than Category. Administrators set field values.

PriorityOverrideReason.title: Priority Override Reason
PriorityOverrideReason.description: The reason why a priority should be changed or edited.

IsMajorIncident.title: Major Incident
IsMajorIncident.description: Indicates whether the incident is business-critical. If set to true, the incident is widespread and business-critical. The default value is false.
